1. BigVGAN: scratch (clean-room) reimplementation policy
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The NVIDIA BigVGAN reference implementation is distributed under the
NVIDIA Source Code License-NC (non-commercial), which is incompatible with
Vokra's Apache 2.0 licensing. Vokra therefore does not use, port, or derive
code from the NVIDIA reference implementation. The BigVGAN-compatible
vocoder operator in Vokra will be reimplemented from scratch based on the
published paper only.

Timing note: this is a forward-looking policy statement. The BigVGAN
operator is not implemented in the current v0.1 spike (milestone M0); it is
planned for a future release, scheduled together with the models that
require it (see docs/milestones.md §1.3).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. NVIDIA CUDA / cuDNN / cuBLAS runtime dependencies (not bundled)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vokra does not bundle or redistribute any NVIDIA runtime component
(CUDA runtime / cudart, cuDNN, cuBLAS). When the CUDA backend is enabled,
Vokra detects a system-installed CUDA at runtime via dynamic loading
(e.g. dlopen("libcuda.so") on Linux, LoadLibrary("nvcuda.dll") on Windows).
Installing NVIDIA components and accepting the corresponding NVIDIA EULAs
is the responsibility of the end user or integrating developer. cuDNN is
never a hard requirement of Vokra.

Timing note: the CUDA backend is planned for the v0.5-v1.0 releases and is
not part of the current v0.1 spike.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. pocketfft (algorithm reference for the CPU FFT implementation)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vokra's CPU FFT lowering (crates/vokra-ops/src/fft/*) is a from-scratch Rust
reimplementation of the algorithm of pocketfft by Martin Reinecke
(https://gitlab.mpcdf.mpg.de/mtr/pocketfft), distributed under the 3-clause
BSD license, Copyright (C) 2010-2019 Max-Planck-Society. The full license
text is reproduced in crates/vokra-ops/THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/pocketfft-LICENSE.txt.

